title: Jaguars sign former Pack LB James-Michael Johnson
text: Updated: 5:55 pm RENO, Nev. (Mynews4.com & KRNV) -- Former Nevada linebacker James-Michael Johnson has found a new NFL home. The Jacksonville Jauguars signed Johnson to their active roster after working out for the team on Monday. Johnson was with Kansas City this preseason but was waived and claimed by Tampa Bay. He played in the Bucs' season opener on special teams but was waived after suffering an undisclosed injury. In his NFL career, Johnson has logged time in 43 regular season games while racking up 88 tackles and 15 special teams tackles.
